<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MOVIE-GUIDE-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MOVIES RECENTLY REVIEWED IN THE BOSTON GLOBE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
!! 1/2 ``Bandits'' Four women break out of a German prison van and
take it on the lam _ to a pounding rock score that expresses their
anger, but makes the film seem an overextended music video. It's
too sentimental and ultimately too empty to take very seriously,
but its partying energies and embattled verve make it hard to
dislike. (R) 
 
!! 1/2 ``The Bone Collector'' Denzel Washington keeps us focused on
his quadriplegic cop threading his way through a maze of clues left
by a grisly serial killer. Angelina Jolie impressively makes us
feel everything her rookie cop feels, acting as Washington's eyes
and ears on the streets and in the sewers. But the body parts never
quite come together in this dark thriller. There's not enough
texture, and the ending is a letdown. (R) 
 
!! 1/2 ``The Insider'' Ungainly in its structuring, pacing, and
pile-driving technique, this film nevertheless tells an important
story forcefully and arrestingly. Two stories, really _ one about
big tobacco being called to task, the other about how complicated
muckraking has grown since Watergate. Russell Crowe is compellingly
complex as the tobacco-company researcher who blew the whistle, but
the story's moral center is Al Pacino's TV producer, who fights to
get the story aired in undiluted form. Christopher Plummer's
flamboyant Mike Wallace is a plus, too. (R) 
 
!!! ``Show Me Love'' This endearing little teen film plays like a
Beatles film without the Beatles. It takes place in a Swedish
backwater and is propelled by director Lukas Moodysson's empathy
with the desperate boredom afflicting its characters, especially
Alexandra Dahlstrom's little pepperpot and Rebecca Liljeberg as
Agnes, who wants to be a writer. Brighter than the rest, Agnes is
suffering because of it, and because she's unable to figure out how
to tell Dahlstrom she's crazy about her. (Unrated)
<TEXT>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
