<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`BESIEGED' TOP BERTOLUCCI; `BLACKTOP' IS TERRIFIC 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Besieged'' _ Bernardo Bertolucci, the director
of great films such as ``The Conformist'' and ``Last Tango in
Paris,'' returns to the subjects of politics, love, and loyalty.
Superb camerawork and complex characters make this a profound
turnaround from such silliness as ``Stealing Beauty.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Two-Lane Blacktop'' _ When the road movie, starring pop
performers Dennis Wilson and James Taylor, was released in 1971, an
Esquire cover story proclaimed it the film of the decade. It's not.
But it is a terrific movie directed by the wildly underrated Monte
Hellman. The soundtrack is superb, and the widescreen remaster is
gorgeous.
</P>
<P>
   ``Broken Vessels'' _ As far as I know, this independent film
didn't have a theatrical release and is heading straight to video
even after winning the Audience Award at the Los Angeles Film
Festival. The story of two paramedics has its problems, but it's a
fascinating character study that goes over the top.
</P>
<P>
   ``Resurrection'' _ NBA fans can spot former Celtic, now Laker
Rick Fox, in this routine, gimmicky action film starring the
laconic Christopher Lambert, who is upstaged by a car chase.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DVD UPDATE: Jim Carrey's ``Liar Liar'' ($35) is better on disc
because it includes a deleted opening scene and some zany outtakes
of Carrey's carrying on. Director Tom Shadyac, who provides helpful
commentary, is as quiet and shy as Carrey is loud and boisterous.
It makes for a winning team.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Nov. 9: ``Notting Hill,'' ``Life Is
Beautiful'' (dubbed English version), ``Instinct,'' ``Heaven,''
``Pal Joey'' (DVD), ``Sore Losers,'' ``Black and White,''
``Strangers,'' ``Ma Vie en Rose'' (DVD), ``Break Up,''
``Heartbeeps,'' ``The Milky Way,'' ``Rogue Trader.'' Nov. 16:
``Austin Powers: The Spy Who Shagged Me,'' ``The Loss of Sexual
Innocence,'' ``Tea With Mussolini,'' ``The Last Picture Show''
(DVD), ``The Castle,'' ``Dr. Akaki.'' Nov. 23: ``The Haunting,''
``The Iron Giant,'' ``The Autumn Tale,'' ``The Draughtsman's
Contract'' (DVD), ``A Zed and Two Noughts'' (DVD), ``Entrapment,''
``South Park: Bigger, Longer and Uncut.'' Nov. 30: ``Wild Wild
West,'' ``Deep Blue Sea.'' Dec. 7: ``Hoods,'' ``Inspector Gadget.''
Dec. 14: ``The General's Daughter,'' ``The Harmonists,'' ``The Very
Thought of You,'' ``A Knight in Camelot,'' ``Drop Dead Gorgeous,''
``Teaching Mrs. Tingle.'' Dec. 21: ``Summer of Sam,'' ``Super Cop
2.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
