<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX _ In Arizona politics, everybody has a favorite John
McCain story. One of them goes like this.
</P>
<P>
   In 1982, having just moved to the state to begin his political
career, McCain was engaged in a bitter race for a seat in Congress.
One of his opponents called his ex-wife, fishing for dirt about the
candidate. When he heard of this, McCain cornered the man at a
