   If you are unlucky, golf in southern Africa can mean being
trampled by an elephant, scragged by umbrella thorns, or surprised
by naked muggers with leaves in their hair, as happened to two lady
golfers recently in Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
   But golf is sometimes a game that needs a bit of added spice.
For golfers of spirit, your correspondent recommends three
memorable African courses.
</P>
<P>
   The first, Katima Mulilo Golf Club, is in the Caprivi region of
