<P>
   DEPOT-EXPO _ With the opening Thursday of metro Atlanta's second
Home Depot Expo, the Atlanta-based retailer has dramatically
changed the upscale concept since the first Expo opened in Atlnta
The new concept aims at the interior designer market, with lots of
custom-made baths, ceramic tile and more rugs and lighting. This
new store is part of Home Depot's recent nationwide expansion of
200 stores. (Bond, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   HEALTHCARE _ A new survey of employers finds that Atlanta and
national health-care costs will rise by 8 percent to 10 percent in
2000. The survey, by Hewatt Associates, covers 600 employers, with
16 based in metro Atlanta. The results demonstrate again that
employers are facing big increases in benefits costs after
relatively flat years in the mid-1990s. (Miller, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
