<P>
   INTERNET2 _ AUSTIN, Texas _ For all the public's fascination
with the Internet, there is a group of more than 120 U.S.
universities that believe it is ``catatonic'' and working on
Internet2. The new Internet would be some 10 times faster and
restricted at first to its creators and reach further. We take a
look at what's going to change our childrens' lives. (Cocks, Austin
American-Statesman). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MP3-PLAY _ DAYTON, Ohio _ A hot trend in music is to download
music purchases directly over the Internet for storage and play
through personal computers. Several companies are now marketing
small, portable players capable of playing music recorded in the
Internet's MP3 format. The latest portable MP3 player is the I-Jam,
introduced by the I-Jam Multimedia Corp. of Illinois. (Cummings,
Dayton Daily News). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TECH-WEBHEALTH _ AUSTIN, Texas _ The coalition of leaders of top
Internet health sites assembled by former Surgeon General C.
Everett Koop said this week it had taken its first steps to address
the lack of ethical standards in the new industry and made plans
for regular discussions over the next five months. (Park, Austin
American-Statesman). MOVED.
