 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Editors,
</P>
<P>
   Papers that used BC-DRUG-MERGER, filed Friday for Saturday
release, may wish to use the following correction:
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article about the proposed merger
between Warner-Lambert and American Home Products and Pfizer's
hostile bid for Warner-Lambert mischaracterized, in its final
paragraph, Friday's closing price of another drug company,
Schering-Plough. That price, $56.6875, was not the stock's 52-week
high; Schering-Plough reached that mark on April 12, at $60.8125.
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service.
</P>
