<P>
   TRUCKERS (Los Angeles) _ Long-haul truckers say California has
the worst drivers and ranks among the states with the worst roads,
particularly the 5 and 10 freeways, according to a new survey.
Those freeways were tied for the second worst in the nation, behind
the 10 in Louisiana. The survey of 1,115 long-haul drivers was
conducted by Overdrive magazine. By Steve Carney. (Will move on
``n'' California news wire.).
</P>
<P>
   KIDS (Los Angeles) _ A new study of California children county
by county finds that nearly 40 percent of children in Los Angeles
County under age five live below the poverty level. Statewide
average is 30 percent of infants live in poverty and one in five
does not have health insurance. And in most counties, the average
cost of childcare accounts for a third of a full-time, mininum-wage
income. Throw in rent and there's no money for food, clothes,
medicine and trips to disneyland. The study is done by Today
Children Now. By Phillip Browne. (Will move on ``n'' California
news wire.)
</P>
