<P>
   Here are the stories New York Times editors are planning for
Page 1, Tuesday, Nov. 9. The N.Y. Times News Service Night
Supervisor is Pat Ryan; phone: (888) 346-9867; e-mail:
patryan(at)nytimes.com.
</P>
<P>
   TOP
</P>
<P>
   Lead story:
</P>
<P>
   HEALTHCARE-INSURE (Undated) _ In a dramatic break with a
longstanding element of managed care that infuriated many doctors
and frustrated their patients, United Health Group says it is
giving up its veto power over medical decision making. United, one
of the nation's biggest managed care companies, says that a
patient's doctor, not the insurance company, will now be able to
decide whether to admit health plan members to a hospital or
provide other treatment. By Milt Freudenheim. (We plan to move the
story by 8:30 p.m. ET in ``w'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   The story runs under a 3-column photo.
</P>
