<P>
   CHINA-SECT (Beijing) _ Chinese officials offer the first
official tally of the government crackdown on the banned Falun Gong
spiritual movement, saying 111 people have been formally arrested
on a variety of criminal charges, from disrupting state security to
stealing state secrets. By Elisabeth Rosenthal. (The story has
moved in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   POPE-GEORGIA (Tbilisi, Georgia) _ Pope John Paul II meets with
the patriarch of the Georgian Orthodox Church in an encounter that
visibly illustrates the lingering obstacles to the pope's longtime
dream of reconciling the Roman Catholic Church and Eastern
Orthodoxy. By Alessandra Stanley. (The story has moved in ``i''
news file.)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-HOSPITAL-INFECTION (Undated) _ According to the Centers for
Disease Control and Prevention, 5 percent of the people admitted to
hospitals, about 1.8 million patients a year, will pick up an
infection there. The cause is simple: Doctors and nurses often
don't wash their hands between patients. By Emily Yoffe. (The story
has moved in ``a'' news file.) 1,750 words.
</P>
