11-08 -- Students at Summerhill practice the rigors of
self-government through the forum of weekly meetings. Despite the
remarkable self-assuredness of the student body, the British
government threatened to close the school last spring after
inspectors from the Office for Standards in Education concluded
that ``Summerhill is not providing an adequate education for its
