<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CORRECTIONS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR TUESDAY, NOVEMBER 9
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Tuesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-KURZWEIL-COMPUTE-NYT (moved on Friday, Nov. 5)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, Nov. 5,
about the possibility of physically linking the human brain to
computers misstated the medical condition of Ray Kurzweil, the
author of a book on the subject. He wrote a previous book about
nutrition because his family has a history of heart disease; it is
not he who has congenital heart disease.
</P>
</TEXT>
