<HEADLINE>
IT LOOKS AS IF PALMER WON'T BE BACK UNTIL 2000
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Official word could come as early as tonight that
injured USC quarterback Carson Palmer will not return this season.
</P>
<P>
   Palmer, who broke his collarbone in September, is scheduled to
be examined by team doctors after today's practice. Even if he is
allowed to begin upper-body exercises this week, he would probably
not have enough time to get in shape and begin throwing to be
available for the Nov. 20 UCLA game.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't want to put him in a position where he overcompensates
and hurts himself,'' USC coach Paul Hackett said.
</P>
<P>
   The Trojans also have little desire to bring Palmer back and
burn his redshirt year just to play in the final two games of the
season. If Palmer redshirts, he would have three years of
eligibility remaining.
</P>
<P>
   ``If he gets hurt again, he'll have that extra year left,''
Hackett said.
</P>
<P>
   __ Howard commits: Banning High tailback Chris Howard orally
committed to USC on Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Howard rushed for 2,495 yards and 33 touchdowns last season.
This season, he rushed for 1,147 yards and 12 touchdowns.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think USC's getting the best running back in the state,''
Banning coach Ed Lalau said.
</P>
<P>
   USC now has eight commitments.
</P>
<P>
   __ Fox expected to start: Hackett said he is leaning toward
starting John Fox against Washington State, with Mike Van Raaphorst
the backup.
</P>
<P>
   ``My opinion is with repetitions, John will continue to
improve,'' Hackett said. ``He did some good things. He just made
one bad throw.''
</P>
<P>
   In a slight difference, Hackett said Fox's performance could
determine how much time he plays against the Cougars. Last week, he
said Van Raaphorst would share playing time with Fox.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't know if I'll do that the next time,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Hackett also said he did not second-guess himself for removing
Fox in the second half and playing Van Raaphorst.
</P>
<P>
   ``In looking at the tape. . . . Mike gave us a lift,'' Hackett
said.
</P>
<P>
   __ Defending Newbury: After viewing the tape, Hackett said
kicker David Newbury was not completely responsible for his missed
field goal and missed extra point.
</P>
<P>
   ``On the missed field goal, there was a lot of pressure on the
left side of the line, and the snap rolled back on the extra
point,'' Hackett said.
</P>
<P>
   __ USC-UCLA game time: The USC-UCLA game at the Coliseum will
kickoff at 12:30 p.m. and be televised on Channel 7 (ABC-TV). The
game is a near-sellout with fewer than 1,000 tickets remaining.
</P>
<P>
   __ Pass happy: USC is on pace to set a school record for passes
attempted in a season. The Trojans are averaging 40 passes a game,
above the school record of 36.6 attempts per game in 1993.
</P>
<P>
   USC has averaged 46 passes during its five-game losing streak
and only 24 rushing attempts. Despite that lopsided ratio, the
Trojans have passed 52 percent of its plays and run 48 percent this
season.
</P>
<P>
   __ Late game: This is the latest USC has faced Washington State
since 1935, when the game was Nov. 16, and the latest meeting the
teams have ever had in Pullman, Wash.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
